# Lint Next.js + Feature Code Quality

Perform comprehensive code quality analysis for Next.js/React feature-based architecture:

**Architecture Quality:**
- Layer separation (Component → Action → Use Case → Repository)
- No layer skipping (Component must NOT call Repository directly)
- Proper dependency injection in Actions
- executePromise wrapper in ALL Use Cases
- ClientResult pattern followed
- No Repository → Repository dependencies

**Next.js/React Standards:**
- ESLint compliance (Next.js config)
- TypeScript strict mode compliance
- Proper "use client"/"use server" directives
- React Hook Form best practices
- Zod schema validation patterns

**Code Quality:**
- Type organization (DTO in *-type.ts, Response internal, Props local)
- No Response types exported from repositories
- No Props types in *-type.ts files
- Proper error handling (executePromise, ClientResult)
- No hardcoded strings (should use constants/i18n)

**Code Smells:**
- Code duplication
- Complex functions (too many responsibilities)
- Missing error handling
- Business logic in wrong layer (Component/Action instead of Use Case)
- UI logic in Use Case
- try/catch instead of executePromise in Use Cases

**Testing:**
- Tests exist for Actions and Use Cases
- Test utils file exists (*-test-utils.ts)
- 3-4 essential test cases per function
- No duplicate global mocks

Provides specific improvements with code examples following project patterns from `features/checkout/`.

**Agent Used:** May invoke `architecture-validator-agent`.

## Usage
```
/lint [file_path]
```

## Parameters
- `file_path`: Path to the file to analyze for code quality (required)
